This file provides configuration data for a list of chips. The
'family' attribute must be present and a supported value, one of:
Boards are one or more chips with some specific parameters, such as
external memory sizes. While any config can be applied to either a
chip or a board's chip, usually only boards will do so since
some board configs will override NFP toolchain command line
arguments, while others like memory regions can only be shrunk on
the command line (the config sizes are maximum).
* iX.emem.base: String value, converted to uint64 when used.
* iX.emem.alloc_base: String value, converted to uint64 when used.
* iX.emem.size: String value, converted to uint64 when used.

_comment: This is the top-level chip for NFP-4xxx and it usesa family ID of 'nfp4000' here, but once the NFP-4xxxspecific family data is loaded, this needs to behandled as if it was an 'nfp6000'. This is becauseNFP-4xxx is, from a chipdata viewpoint, the sameas an NFP-6xxx with some islands removed/disabledand no ILA CPP Target. Describing this as a separatefamily in chipdata is cleaner and more readable,but to any chipdata user the NFP-4xxx and NFP-6xxxfamilies are the same.
